Highly recommended. All my years cooking as a personal chef, this is my first prime rib roast. This recipe is wonderful, delicious and EASY. I marinated for 24 hours, and used the mortar and pestle to make my paste. I finished each slice of meat with Brittney Grey sea salt, as the rub is not overly salty. Whenever I roast anything, I always put a quartered onion in the bottom of the roasting pan. This way, when it comes time to make your jus or gravy, you have a caramelized onion to add flavor, texture and depth. It's something my mother always did, and I have continued to always roast meat in this manner. I will continue to make this for Xmas dinner; my husband and son thought it was heavenly. My roast was a regular grocery store $3.59 a pound holiday special. It was 5.66# and I used the entire recipe for the rub. I took off the ties and put some of the rub in the flap above the bone and retied it before roasting. I am pleased with removing so much fat before rubbing and cooking. It yielded plenty despite the meager layer left on the meat.

